£Ό@939814b676b21d81091a511e9dbd97257a8a60a33ea29a2fc40494957a2682acΎTitle: title: export module
Path: Examples
Content:
Define a custom command in a submodule of a module and call it.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam {
        export module eggs {
            export def foo [] { "foo" }
        }
    }
    use spam eggs
    eggs foo
foo

```
